Sentencas: The performance of two-cell planar solid oxide fuel cell stacks using coal syngas, with and without hydrogen sulfide (H2S), was studied.
Titulo: Effects of coal syngas and H2S on the performance of solid oxide fuel cells Part 2.: Stack tests

Sentencas: All cells were tested at 850 degrees C with a constant current load of 15.2 A (current density of 0.22 A cm(-2) per cell) and 30% fuel utilization.
Titulo: Effects of coal syngas and H2S on the performance of solid oxide fuel cells Part 2.: Stack tests

Sentencas: The H2S injection immediately and significantly affected the power degradation of the stack system regardless of the carrier fuel.
Titulo: Effects of coal syngas and H2S on the performance of solid oxide fuel cells Part 2.: Stack tests

Sentencas: Results for the test with only H-2 and N-2 in the presence of H2S (119-120 ppm) indicated that the power decay and area-specific resistance (ASR) degradation values were lower than those for the tests where simulated syngas containing CO and increased water content was used.
Titulo: Effects of coal syngas and H2S on the performance of solid oxide fuel cells Part 2.: Stack tests

Sentencas: The results indicate that contact points in the stack contributed to the power degradation of the system.
Titulo: Effects of coal syngas and H2S on the performance of solid oxide fuel cells Part 2.: Stack tests

Sentencas: Other factors, including contamination from the upstream fuel gas tubing, may have contributed to the higher degradation under simulated syngas conditions.
Titulo: Effects of coal syngas and H2S on the performance of solid oxide fuel cells Part 2.: Stack tests

Sentencas: In general the data confirm previous results for single cell testing, and showed that for this specific short stacks (two-cells) arrangement both a fast and a slow response to H,S injection that eventually stabilized.
Titulo: Effects of coal syngas and H2S on the performance of solid oxide fuel cells Part 2.: Stack tests
